Have you got any idea what's going on in Japan for the last 30 or so years?
Up until the 90s, distribution and possession of CP was perfectly legal in Japan, and the only reason they eventually banned distribution in the 90s was because of the UN constantly pressuring them to do so along with many major Western countries. Until 2014 possession of CP was still legal in Japan, but again, the decade long pressure coming from the UN to ban anything involving child sexualization had them give in. 2006 and 2010 were other big push years for the UN, driven by incidents like rapelay and britney spears unknowingly cosplaying as a loli from a hentai manga. Risque child modeling that dance the line, and junior idol stuff are still a thing there, proving that the concept of pedophilia doesn't only have purely negative connotations in that culture. 
Since Japan has been culturally isolated and xenophobic for a long time some of their cultural values have been literally stuck at a place where the West was in the 60s. Sexually positive, but with that sense of privacy still intact. They never had a sexual revolution, or feminism, which was a large driving force in the west to ban child porn based on feefees and 'muh slippery slope'. Going forward, you will see Japan slowly enact the same moral standards that have been enshrined in the West for decades. It's not going to happen tomorrow, but there is no stopping it. Sexualizing childhood is still a big part of Japanese culture(for better or worse) and changing that requires people with the wrong mindset to die off and be replaced with a more enlightened peoplekind.
